# Core traffic/queue-chain functions that MUST hold 100% statement
# coverage — stricter than the repo-wide >=95% package gate, and NOT
# waivable by the OS-bound coverage allowlist (these functions live in
# allowlisted packages like agent/internal/platform/darwin, so the
# package-level gate would never catch a regression here).
#
# Rationale: user directive 2026-06-10 — the four core chains (ai-gateway
# traffic, desktop-agent traffic, compliance-proxy traffic, hub
# consume+persist) are performance- and correctness-critical; a dropped
# branch in their hot path is a billing/compliance/availability defect.
# Concurrency correctness (no data race, no cross-flow bleed, fail-open)
# is only trustworthy when every branch is exercised.
#
# Format: one entry per line — "<module-relative-package-dir> <FuncName>".
# '#' comments and blank lines ignored. A receiver method is named by its
# bare function name (e.g. "Enqueue", not "(*Writer).Enqueue").
#
# Adding or REMOVING an entry requires explicit user approval (same
# discipline as scripts/.coverage-allowlist). Enforced by
# scripts/check-core-path-coverage.sh (pre-commit + CI).
#
# OS-tagged packages (darwin/linux/windows) are only buildable on their
# GOOS; the checker SKIPS (does not fail) a package that does not build on
# the current platform, so darwin entries are enforced on macOS pre-commit
# and OS-neutral entries everywhere.

# --- desktop-agent traffic chain: macOS NE flow decision (lock-free concurrent) ---
packages/agent/internal/platform/darwin handleNewFlow
packages/agent/internal/platform/darwin decideFlow
packages/agent/internal/platform/darwin handleFlowUpdateHost
packages/agent/internal/platform/darwin handleFlowClosed
packages/agent/internal/platform/darwin storeFlow
packages/agent/internal/platform/darwin loadFlow
packages/agent/internal/platform/darwin loadAndDeleteFlow
packages/agent/internal/platform/darwin LookupFlowDestination
packages/agent/internal/platform/darwin reply
packages/agent/internal/platform/darwin passthroughFrame
packages/agent/internal/platform/darwin decisionString

# --- desktop-agent traffic chain: SQLite audit queue drain ---
packages/agent/internal/observability/audit/queue drainOnce

# --- desktop-agent traffic chain: process-metadata cache (darwin) ---
packages/agent/internal/platform/darwin/proc ProcessInfoCached

# --- desktop-agent traffic chain: shared PID-keyed process cache (linux/windows) ---
packages/agent/internal/platform/pidcache Get
packages/agent/internal/platform/pidcache New
packages/agent/internal/platform/pidcache sweepExpiredLocked

# --- ai-gateway traffic chain: traffic_event writer ---
packages/ai-gateway/internal/platform/audit Enqueue
packages/ai-gateway/internal/platform/audit flush
packages/ai-gateway/internal/platform/audit publishRecord
